French Painter, Nicolas Taunay,

00:04:15.220 --> 00:04:19.410
to Brazilian photography
and childhood histories.

00:04:19.410 --> 00:04:22.760
She's currently curating
an exhibit

00:04:22.760 --> 00:04:25.200
at the [speaking
foreign language] title,

00:04:25.200 --> 00:04:26.500
[speaking foreign
language], which consists

00:04:26.500 --> 00:04:28.480
of a yearlong programs of
exhibits, workshops and lectures

00:04:28.480 --> 00:04:30.320
on the [speaking
foreign language],

00:04:30.320 --> 00:04:32.580
I tried look up a translation.

00:04:32.580 --> 00:04:34.510
I think, ebbs and flows.

00:04:34.510 --> 00:04:38.820
Between Africa, the Americas,
the Caribbean and Europe.

00:04:38.820 --> 00:04:41.320
We look forward to that in 2018,

00:04:41.320 --> 00:04:43.550
if we can all go
to Brazil for that.

00:04:43.550 --> 00:04:46.560
As you can imagine, all this
work has been recognized

00:04:46.560 --> 00:04:49.060
with some of the most
important national

00:04:49.060 --> 00:04:51.570
and international
prizes and fellowships,

00:04:51.570 --> 00:04:53.460
including five Jabuti Prizes,

00:04:53.460 --> 00:04:55.520
which is Brazil's
leading literary prize.

00:04:55.520 --> 00:04:58.810
And the Brazilian
Academy of Letters Prize.

00:04:58.810 --> 00:05:00.990
She also holds a
Guggenheim fellowship

00:05:00.990 --> 00:05:03.400
from the Guggenheim Foundation

00:05:03.400 --> 00:05:08.790
and the John Carter Brown
Library University fellowship

00:05:08.790 --> 00:05:10.090
as well.

00:05:10.090 --> 00:05:12.970
She's been a visitor at
Oxford, Leiden, Princeton

00:05:12.970 --> 00:05:17.410
and Brown Universities, a Tinker
Professor at Columbia University

00:05:17.410 --> 00:05:20.920
and since 2011 she
is Global Professor

00:05:20.920 --> 00:05:24.480
at Princeton University.

00:05:24.480 --> 00:05:26.890
She writes regularly for
the Brazilian newspapers,

00:05:26.890 --> 00:05:31.240
Folha de S Paulo, Estado
de S. Paulo and Nexo.

00:05:31.240 --> 00:05:34.360
And since 2015 she's a
co-curator for history

00:05:34.360 --> 00:05:37.490
for the Museum of
Art in Sao Paulo.

00:05:37.490 --> 00:05:40.990
Today she'll be here
talking about Lima Barreto.

00:05:40.990 --> 00:05:45.190
After her talk we'll have a
conversation with Bryan McCann

00:05:45.190 --> 00:05:48.660
and the audience, so
please stay for that.

00:05:48.660 --> 00:05:52.510
Please join me in welcoming
Lilia to the Library.

00:05:52.510 --> 00:05:56.500
