01:07:40.400 --> 01:07:45.730
that you can see exactly how
he's playing with colors.

01:07:45.730 --> 01:07:49.270
In my opinion, Lima Barreto
writes a black literature

01:07:49.270 --> 01:07:54.860
in Brazil, because first of all,
the main characters are black

01:07:54.860 --> 01:07:57.440
or mestizos or mulattos.

01:07:57.440 --> 01:08:00.540
He uses a lot of names.

01:08:00.540 --> 01:08:03.510
Olives, he describes
himself like black olive.

01:08:03.510 --> 01:08:05.360
Something like this.

01:08:05.360 --> 01:08:08.630
And then he's also
he's a black writer,

01:08:08.630 --> 01:08:11.710
because color matters for him.

01:08:11.710 --> 01:08:14.970
So, if you put together
Clara dos Anjos names

01:08:14.970 --> 01:08:19.670
in these two paragraphs and
he tries to describe Joaquim,

01:08:19.670 --> 01:08:22.850
Clara dos Anjos father,
