white, cannot be black.

01:08:55.570 --> 01:08:59.230
So, you can see what
Lima Barreto was trying

01:08:59.230 --> 01:09:01.550
to say with this, no?

01:09:01.550 --> 01:09:04.370
And the deception,
the suddenness

01:09:04.370 --> 01:09:09.060
of Clara dos Anjos
it's very impressive.

01:09:09.060 --> 01:09:12.320
One thing that touched
me a lot is

01:09:12.320 --> 01:09:15.920
that he started writing
Clara dos Anjos

01:09:15.920 --> 01:09:19.100
in the first moment he
started writing his diary.

01:09:19.100 --> 01:09:25.130
900. And the first
version of Clara dos Anjos,

01:09:25.130 --> 01:09:27.530
she ends like a prostitute

01:09:27.530 --> 01:09:34.590
and in another version
he kills Cassi Jones.

01:09:34.590 --> 01:09:37.780
In another version
she's pregnant.

01:09:37.780 --> 01:09:43.230
This is the version we know,
because the last one he signed.

01:09:43.230 --> 01:09:47.430
But this is very important for
me, because the critics use it

01:09:47.430 --> 01:09:52.900
to say that Lima Barreto
was like writer in a hurry,

01:09:52.900 --> 01:09:55.960
that he had no time
to finish his books.

01:09:55.960 --> 01:10:01.470
But I think that Lima Barreto
uses another very modern

01:10:01.470 --> 01:10:03.990
[inaudible] of unfinished.

01:10:03.990 --> 01:10:09.800
Most of his stories he's
frequently rewriting

01:10:09.800 --> 01:10:11.120
the stories.

01:10:11.120 --> 01:10:16.860
Sometimes as a short story,
sometimes as a chronicle,

01:10:16.860 --> 01:10:19.260
sometimes as a journalist.

01:10:19.260 --> 01:10:24.370
So it's very impressive to
me that he kept the name.

01:10:24.370 --> 01:10:27.790
This one since the beginning
of the novel, Clara dos Anjos.

01:10:27.790 --> 01:10:29.330
&gt;&gt; I read the book
many years ago,

01:10:29.330 --> 01:10:32.970
and I don't remember the
descriptions of mother

01:10:32.970 --> 01:10:35.250
and father or father
and [inaudible].

