edition of the roots of Brazil

01:11:07.960 --> 01:11:10.640
and we tried to show how

01:11:10.640 --> 01:11:16.040
and when [inaudible]
changed his book completely.

01:11:16.040 --> 01:11:20.900
So we had the five most
important editions.

01:11:20.900 --> 01:11:25.430
And we tried to prove
how this is Brazil,

01:11:25.430 --> 01:11:27.990
it is a book that moves.

01:11:27.990 --> 01:11:32.840
It's not the same book in
36 and the last version

01:11:32.840 --> 01:11:35.260
that [speaking foreign
language] put in that.

01:11:35.260 --> 01:11:38.350
The same thing happens
with Clara dos Anjos.

01:11:38.350 --> 01:11:43.050
So, I agree and I disagree
with you, because depending

01:11:43.050 --> 01:11:51.460
on the end, she is a person
that can just be a sad person

01:11:51.460 --> 01:11:54.360
and sometimes she's
a person that fights.

01:11:54.360 --> 01:11:58.020
So, this is the category
you have unfinished.

01:11:58.020 --> 01:12:00.350
So, depending on the
version, you are dealing

01:12:00.350 --> 01:12:04.510
with the last one, the one he
signed, but the one he signed,

01:12:04.510 --> 01:12:07.720
in my opinion, it's
not the last one.

01:12:09.970 --> 01:12:12.040
And that's literature, no?

01:12:12.040 --> 01:12:15.510
That's the power of
literature, imagination.

01:12:15.510 --> 01:12:17.220
&gt;&gt; Bryan McCann:
That's beautiful.

