01:15:12.120 --> 01:15:17.130
Because I think diversity
is always more.

01:15:17.130 --> 01:15:18.870
That we need diversity.

01:15:18.870 --> 01:15:21.620
That we'll have a
better university

01:15:21.620 --> 01:15:24.590
if you have more
diversity in the university.

01:15:24.590 --> 01:15:27.130
And I'm not talking
just about the students.

01:15:27.130 --> 01:15:30.690
I'm talking about the
public administration,

01:15:30.690 --> 01:15:33.060
I'm talking about
the professors.

01:15:33.060 --> 01:15:36.470
So, if I look around
I'm always --

01:15:36.470 --> 01:15:39.670
now I'm always for
affirmative action.

01:15:39.670 --> 01:15:47.180
At that moment my thought in
race as a biological catholic,

01:15:47.180 --> 01:15:48.510
I use it to say things
like this.

01:15:48.510 --> 01:15:53.300
We do not have racist,
we have one race.

01:15:53.300 --> 01:15:54.600
So, what's wrong.

01:15:54.600 --> 01:15:58.980
But then for a long time in
working with social race,

01:15:58.980 --> 01:16:02.150
like Bryan asked me
in a very casual way.

01:16:02.150 --> 01:16:04.210
So, if you think
about social race,

01:16:04.210 --> 01:16:07.290
what we are saying is
we are in one race,

01:16:07.290 --> 01:16:15.940
but the social creates this very
hot difference in our society.

01:16:15.940 --> 01:16:19.200
And as an anthropologist,
because I'm a mix of a historian

01:16:19.200 --> 01:16:21.220
and an anthropologist, I think

01:16:21.220 --> 01:16:25.250
that culture is a
kind of second nature.

01:16:25.250 --> 01:16:27.800
So, it's so strong as nature.

01:16:27.800 --> 01:16:31.060
