the distinction you are making,

01:17:17.090 --> 01:17:24.030
I have had lots of experiences
in my own research talking

01:17:24.030 --> 01:17:28.190
to Brazilians where
they at one point back

01:17:28.190 --> 01:17:39.120
when I was doing my dissertation
research, I handed out surveys

01:17:39.120 --> 01:17:48.090
of a racial category and that
was a very confusing question

01:17:48.090 --> 01:17:53.360
and I got answers that were sort
of boggle the American mind.

01:17:53.360 --> 01:17:58.670
Where people would say
to me, "Well, my race,

01:17:58.670 --> 01:18:04.300
do you mean in the summer when
I have a tan or in the dark

01:18:04.300 --> 01:18:10.840
or in the winter or when
there's not as much sun?"

01:18:10.840 --> 01:18:15.970
And these are things that don't
make any sense to Americans.

01:18:15.970 --> 01:18:22.210
I give that example in my
classes on US based relations.

01:18:22.210 --> 01:18:28.750
So I think these are things that
don't make sense to Americans.

01:18:28.750 --> 01:18:34.010
