01:19:22.600 --> 01:19:23.900
There was a moment when some
of the scholars in Brazil

01:19:23.900 --> 01:19:25.200
in the 30s and 40s used to
describe color and race --

01:19:25.200 --> 01:19:26.500
used to oppose race and color
in a sense that race is --

01:19:26.500 --> 01:19:27.800
color is better than race.

01:19:27.800 --> 01:19:29.100
Color is [inaudible]
and race is not.

01:19:29.100 --> 01:19:30.400
I do not agree with that.

01:19:30.400 --> 01:19:31.700
I think that color is
a very perverse system.

01:19:31.700 --> 01:19:37.050
Very [inaudible] naturalized,
invisible form of racist.

01:19:37.050 --> 01:19:41.940
And more than this,
it's a very private form

01:19:41.940 --> 01:19:44.060
of dealing with racist.

01:19:44.060 --> 01:19:48.600
The thing is, in public's
view, we are not going to talk

01:19:48.600 --> 01:19:52.930
about this, but in private, yes.

01:19:52.930 --> 01:20:01.060
And color is a -- I think
it's a very very complex way

01:20:01.060 --> 01:20:03.050
of classification.

01:20:03.050 --> 01:20:05.970
It's a social marker
of difference.

01:20:05.970 --> 01:20:11.330
That you put together
different marks like color,

01:20:11.330 --> 01:20:15.190
class, sometimes region.

01:20:15.190 --> 01:20:17.120
Sometimes religion also.

01:20:17.120 --> 01:20:20.990
So, it's a way of not
saying and saying.

01:20:20.990 --> 01:20:27.780
